1. Use correct reactjs build (production / development)\r\n2. Mute some warning only useful in development environment\r\n\r\nThe first one has been there for quite long. Unless you are customizing how react source is loaded, the current implementation will always use the development build. This is really bad, since the development build is slow and takes more size in final build.\r\n\r\nSo, the solution is introducing `React::Config`, an universal config for HyperReact. Currently, it only provide `React::Config.config[:environment]` which by default depending on the value of `RACK_ENV` (already set by Rails , so it should work out of box if you are using Rails) \r\n\r\nThe same config will be serialized and picked up at runtime to disable dev-only warning. To be noticed, the config is readonly in browser context. \r\n\r\nYou can set the environment config yourself as following or simply provide `RACK_ENV`. \r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nReact::Config.environment = 'production'\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe work on this is tracked on #203 \r\n","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby-hyperloop/hyper-react/issues/201","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby-hyperloop/hyper-react","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby-hyperloop/hyper-react/issues/201/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby-hyperloop/hyper-react/issues/201/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ruby-hyperloop/hyper-react/issues/201/events","html_url":"https://github.com/ruby-hyperloop/hyper-react/issues/201","id":199329762,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxOTkzMjk3NjI=","number":201,"title":"Drop ruby 1.9.3 support","user":{"login":"zetachang","id":839973,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjgzOTk3Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/839973?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/zetachang","html_url":"https://github.com/zetachang","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/zetachang/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com